00:15:19.484 --> 00:15:22.054
<i> The CIA and Guantanamo Bay
 are known</i>

00:15:22.087 --> 00:15:24.222
<i> for using
 psychological torture</i>

00:15:24.255 --> 00:15:26.692
<i> involving the anticipation
 of pain</i>

00:15:26.725 --> 00:15:30.228
<i> against prisoners
 in the war on terror.</i>

00:15:30.261 --> 00:15:34.967
The effects of this type
of torture can last a lifetime.

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:36.468
So what's worse?

00:15:36.501 --> 00:15:41.573
Waiting for pain to happen
or the pain itself?

00:15:41.606 --> 00:15:43.542
You might be surprised.

00:15:46.678 --> 00:15:48.647
<i> We're basing our investigation</i>

00:15:48.680 --> 00:15:51.249
<i> on an anticipation of pain
 experiment,</i>

00:15:51.282 --> 00:15:54.252
<i> conducted at the
 University College London,</i>

00:15:54.285 --> 00:15:56.254
<i> which gave subject
 two options.</i>

00:15:56.287 --> 00:15:59.725
<i> Option one: Experience
